<br>
Some people think that's a good thing.  It's not really, unless you can constantly keep your eyes flitting between combat pane, chat pane, and and the main view.<br>
<br>
Brief example, someone in my party says &quot;inc beastie.&quot;  Except I'm not looking at the chat pane, I'm looking at my partymate, and the beastie he's got chasing him.  I run to fight beastie.  Now I flit my eyes occasionally to the combat pane, to look for the text cues I need to see to figure out when I can pull off one of my situational styles (like when I evade the mob's attack).<br>
<br>
Beastie falls, we take a breather, and I flit my eyes down to the chat pane.  WHAT?  &quot;inc beastie&quot;?!?  He pulled another one already?<br>
<br>
Some people may not like the EQ style of having it all in the same window, but it provides a time reference.<br>
<br>
If they insist on keeping messages separate in multiple panes, it would be nice to either have a timestamp or even better yet some sort of message aging (where recent messages are brighter, perhaps, or otherwise emphasized).<br>
<br>
